---
import Layout from "../layouts/BlogPost.astro";
import AboutHeroImage from "../assets/blog-header.png";
---

<Layout
  title="About Me"
  description="Devon Garbalosa — Solutions Engineer at Laravel, dad, national park collector, and someone who writes about the messy human side of building software."
  pubDate={new Date("July 12 2025")}
  heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
  showBackLink={false}
>
  <p>
    I'm Devon Garbalosa. I changed my major from Finance to Information Systems
    because a few Excel formulas made me think software engineering would be
    easy. A decade later, I've learned that the code is hard — but so is
    everything around it. Now I'm a Solutions Engineer at Laravel, the framework
    that lit the fire in the first place.
  </p>

  <h2>The Short Version</h2>
  <p>
    I started in data engineering. Found Laravel. Built internal tools that
    quietly spread through an enterprise because they actually worked. Grew into
    architecture, then leadership — cloud-native systems on AWS, distributed
    teams, and all the relationships, planning, and deadlines that nobody warns
    you about in school.
  </p>
  <p>
    Along the way I visited 34 national parks and became a dad twice. Both
    required more patience than I came wired with.
  </p>

  <h2>What I Actually Do</h2>
  <p>
    At Laravel, I help teams build better applications with the framework I've
    spent years betting my career on. Before that, I built event-driven
    platforms, compliance-aware deployment pipelines, and AI/ML workflows in
    financial services — the kind of work where "move fast and break things"
    gets you a meeting with Legal.
  </p>
  <p>
    I live with ADHD. It shapes everything — how I lead, how I learn, how I
    design systems. I've stopped treating it as a thing to manage and started
    treating it as the lens I build through. It makes me impatient with
    unnecessary friction and obsessive about clarity. Both of those turned out
    to be useful.
  </p>

  <h2>Why This Blog Exists</h2>
  <p>
    I'm a starter by nature. I love the 0-to-1 part — the blank canvas, the
    first commit, the rush of a new idea. Shipping? That's the part where I'm
    kicking and screaming and rewriting the whole damn thing for the fourth
    time. Writing helps me slow down long enough to figure out what I actually
    believe — before the next context switch wipes it clean.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're navigating a career in tech, wrestling with whether to lead or
    build, or just trying to make sense of the noise — something here might
    land. That's the hope, anyway.
  </p>

  <h2>Say Hello</h2>
  <p>
    I'm easy to find. Connect with me on
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/devon-garbalosa/">LinkedIn</a>, follow
    along on <a href="https://x.com/dgarbs51_">X</a>, or check out what I'm
    building on <a href="https://github.com/dgarbs51">GitHub</a>. If something
    I've written resonates — or you think I'm wrong — I want to hear it.
  </p>
</Layout>
